Project: Investigate a Dataset (noshowappointments-kagglev2-may-2016!)¶

Table of Contents¶

  • Introduction
  • Data Wrangling
  • Exploratory Data Analysis
  • Conclusions

Introduction¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row

What factors are important for us to know in order to predict if a patient will show up for their scheduled appointment?. Does some of chronic Diseases is The most common to a specific category

In [6]:
# convert date object columns to DateTime and calculate Waiting days as time delta and creat it as a column
df['ScheduledDay']=pd.to_datetime(df['ScheduledDay'],format=('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S%z')).dt.tz_localize(None)
df['AppointmentDay']=pd.to_datetime(df['AppointmentDay'],format=('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S%z')).dt.tz_localize(None)
timedelta =(df['AppointmentDay']- df['ScheduledDay']).dt.days
df.insert(5,'Waiting_Days',timedelta) # insert the column at suitable index

In [18]:
# define function to facilitate our counts
def count_values(df,column=None):
    return df[column].value_counts()
In [19]:
# Condition establishment for show and no show patients
show=df['No_show']=='No'
no_show=df['No_show']=='Yes'

plt.bar(X_axis[1],df.groupby(["Gender"])[['Hypertension','Diabetes']].get_group('F').sum()[1], width=0.4,color='chocolate',label='Diabetes');
plt.bar(X_axis[0],df.groupby(["Gender"])[['Hypertension','Diabetes']].get_group('M').sum()[1], width=0.4,color='chocolate');
plt.title('chronic diseases',fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Gender',fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Number of Patiants have chronic diseases',fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(X_axis, Gender)
plt.legend()
plt.show()

Hence Female have the Majority of chronic diseases therfore also they have majourity in Attendance

Conclusions¶

  1. There is no effect on the later scheduled appointment on the ratio of attendance
  2. Ages from 0 to 12 years and from 47 to 60 years have regular attendance than the rest of patients
  3. Female are the Majourity in Medical Attendance in contray to Males
  4. Female are the most prone to Chronic Diseases
  5. The impact of social welfare program is very week on the total number of patients as 9.8 % of total patients has Scholarship 7.8% from the total number of patiants had attended
  6. The neighbourhoad relation on attendance The nearest distance the most Attended and vice versa
  7. the successive bar chart tell us the first 10 neighbourhoad that haven't scholarship. first three neighbourhood are frequent attend to this hospital i estimate that this hospital has cheap price
  8. SMS sending Message impact in terms of patiants who recived and attend 72% well but the total number who recived Sms 9.8% from the total patients which mean Sms sending Tool needs to revise ### Limitations
  • Why specifically women who suffer from chronic diseases? This is only a sample of the data. Do the rest of the medical centers have the same percentage?
